# .secret-scan-allow — false-positive allowlist for scripts/Invoke-SecretScan.ps1
#
# One LITERAL allowed value per line. A scan hit is suppressed when the
# matched text CONTAINS any value listed here, so entries also suppress
# themselves when this file is scanned.
#
# Rules:
# - Blank lines and lines starting with '#' are ignored.
# - Allowlist ONLY known false positives (doc examples, synthetic fixtures,
#   public identifiers). Never allowlist a real secret — rotate it instead.
# - Prefer the full matched string as the entry; substrings also match, so
#   keep entries long enough to stay specific.
# - This file must live at the scanned root. Copy it into each repo that
#   adopts the scanner.
#
# Synthetic examples (safe to delete; they are not real credentials):
ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
AKIA0000000000000000
glpat-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
